  "prompt": "Can I glue a tooth filling back into my mouth?",
  "response": "It is not recommended to glue a tooth filling back into your mouth on your own. Dental fillings need to be professionally placed by a dentist to ensure they fit properly and adhere securely to the tooth structure. Attempting to do this yourself could lead to further dental problems, such as improper sealing, damage to the tooth, or infection.\n\nIf you have lost a filling, it's important to contact your dentist as soon as possible. In the meantime, avoid chewing on the affected side and maintain good oral hygiene to prevent further complications. Your dentist will be able to properly assess the situation and provide the appropriate treatment.",
